# S9 : BOOTSTRAPPING STRATEGY
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

§ ZIG-BOOTSTRAP  ← §§ S9.1 ★ reference-model
  § strategy :
    stage0 = pre-built zig1.wasm (committed-to-repo)
    + minimal-wasm2c (4K-LOC purpose-built)
    + system-C-compiler
    → stage1 = zig1 C-output
    stage1 + self-hosted-source
    → stage2 = zig-in-C (built by stage1 + system-cc)
    stage2 + self-hosted-source
    → stage3 = final-optimized-zig
  ✓ chain-of-trust : everything is-auditable-source
  ✓ no-LLVM needed for stage0 path (C-backend-only)
  ✓ O(1) steps : no-per-release-binary-seed
  I> CSSLv3 adopt SAME pattern :
    stage0 : CSSLv3-core written-in-Rust (one-time throwaway)
    stage0 outputs C OR LLVM-IR for platform-seed
    stage1 : self-hosted CSSLv3-compiler built-by stage0
    stage2 : self-optimizing CSSLv3 built-by stage1
    @ stage1 throw-away-Rust-code ¬ maintain-dual-impl
    ∵ avoid Zig-dual-impl maintenance-cost

§ BOOTSTRAP-LANG-CHOICE  ← §§ S9.2
  candidates : Rust • Zig • OCaml
  Rust :
    ✓ mature • MLIR-crate-bindings (mlir-sys)
    ✓ Enzyme-autodiff integration via Rust-fork (autodiff-project-goal)
    ✓ Apocky familiar + active LoA-Rust-repo
    ✓ LLVM-bindings via inkwell
    ✗ compile-time slower
  Zig :
    ✓ no-LLVM-dep @ stage0 possible
    ✓ self-bootstrapping model-already-proven
    ✗ comptime-20×-slow • stability-issues 2025
  OCaml :
    ✓ excellent-for-compiler (effect-handlers + PLT-ecosystem)
    ✗ MLIR-bindings less-mature
    ✗ learning-curve for Apocky (less-familiar)
  ‼ DECISION : Rust for stage0
    ∵ MLIR ecosystem + Enzyme + Apocky-familiarity
    ∵ mlir-sys + melior crate mature-2024-2025
    ∵ LLVM-support first-class

§ MRUST-REFERENCE  ← §§ S9.3
  ○ mrustc : Rust written-in-C++ minimal-Rust-compiler
  ○ bootstrap Rust without prior Rust
  I> CSSLv3 mirror : at-stage3 provide mrustc-style-seed
    ≡ CSSLv3-written-in-C tarball OR C-backend-output-generator
    ≡ bootstrap CSSLv3 without-prior-CSSLv3 tarball

§ DEV-LOOP BOOTSTRAPPING  ← §§ S9.4 practical
  phase-1 (weeks) : Rust-hosted CSSLv3 lexer+parser+AST
  phase-2 (weeks) : type-checker minimal (no-refinement yet)
  phase-3 : MLIR-codegen of cssl.sdf dialect → SPIR-V
  phase-4 : run first LoA-demo-shader in CSSLv3
  phase-5 : add effect-system (F3 minimal)
  phase-6 : add autodiff via Enzyme-pass (F1)
  phase-7 : add refinement-types (F2)
  phase-8 : add staging (F4)
  phase-9 : rewrite Rust-compiler → CSSLv3
  phase-10 : drop Rust-impl

∎ S9
